=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Build the fused 3,6-dimethyl triazolopyrazine N-H core from the corresponding diaminopyrazine/pyridazine precursor by cyclocondensation to give the heterocycle nucleus. | Step 2: In parallel, start from a halopyridine and install the side-chain amino alcohol by SNAr to give a protected 2-(2-hydroxyethyl)-4-halo-5-(protected NC(C)CCO) pyridine intermediate, then convert the side chain to the required 2-(2-bromoethyl) electrophile. | Step 3: Converge the two branches by N-alkylation of the heterocycle N-H core with the pyridyl 2-bromoethyl fragment to form the N-alkylated protected advanced intermediate, Cc1ncc(C)n2nc(CCc3ccc(OR)c(NR’(C)CCO)n3)nc12. | Step 4: Global deprotection/unmasking of the phenol and amino alcohol protections furnishes the target Cc1ncc(C)n2nc(CCc3ccc(O)c(NC(C)CCO)n3)nc12.

